transcript.text: Hey there, welcome to this tutorial on how to create product categories and category groups in your On Print Shop store.
In this video, we'll guide you through the simple steps to organize your products effectively.
Categories and groups make shopping easier for your customers.
They help people find what they want to make their purchase faster.
Here's how you can implement this.
First, log into the On Print Shop Admin panel.
Once you're logged in, you'll be greeted with your store's main interface.
Now navigate to the Product section and here you will find the Product Categories option where you will see the list of categories and groups.
Let's first understand and enable the setting from the Store configuration.
Here, go to the Store Configuration section, then select Site Settings to add the category and Category group.
In the search box, type Category and there you'll see the setting to enable the product category and Group.
In the Product tab from the drop down, select Yes to display the product category on the storefront.
Select No to turn off the product category and select Yes with Group to display the category with group.
Now select Yes with the Group option from the drop down and then save the changes.
Moving ahead, hover to the Product category section and create a product category group Weaver, naming it Promotional Products.
You can add a suitable image for the new category, enable the status to display on the storefront, and finally, click on Save and Back to create the new category group.
Now let's create a new product category and assign it to the Promotional Products group created from the Product category screen.
Click on the Add Product Category button, enter the category title, select Promotional Product as the group.
From the drop down, add the category image, enable the status as Active and save.
Let's take a look at the front store.
Here in the Products menu, you can find the product group, Promotional Products, under which we have the product category Promotional T-shirts and a product T-shirt is assigned to it.
And there you have it.
Creating product categories and category groups in your on print shop store is a breeze.
It's all about ensuring your products are well organized for your customers to find what they're looking for easily.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
